---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Allianz Care in Costa Rica', level: 2 },
  { id: 'caja-strategy', text: 'CAJA + Allianz Strategy', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costa-rica-network', text: 'Network Coverage', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'vs-local-options', text: 'vs Local Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'claims', text: 'Using Your Insurance', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-its-for', text: 'Who Should Choose Allianz', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Costa Rica', href: '/countries/costa-rica/insurance' },
  { title: 'Allianz Care Review', href: '/providers/allianz-care' },
  { title: 'Allianz vs Cigna', href: '/compare/cigna-global-vs-allianz-care' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'crPrice', header: 'Costa Rica (Age 50)' },
  { key: 'deductible', header: 'Deductible Option' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Essential', coverage: 'Inpatient + Emergency', crPrice: '$95-130/mo', deductible: 'Up to $5,000' },
  { plan: 'Classic', coverage: 'Essential + Outpatient', crPrice: '$150-200/mo', deductible: 'Up to $5,000' },
  { plan: 'Premium', coverage: 'Comprehensive', crPrice: '$200-260/mo', deductible: 'Up to $5,000' },
  { plan: 'Platinum', coverage: 'Premium + Enhanced', crPrice: '$250-330/mo', deductible: 'Up to $5,000' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'factor', header: 'Factor' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
  { key: 'local', header: 'CAJA + INS' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { factor: 'Monthly Cost (Age 50)', allianz: '$150-200', local: '~$135 combined' },
  { factor: 'With High Deductible', allianz: '$65-100', local: 'Limited options' },
  { factor: 'Private Hospital Access', allianz: 'Yes', local: 'INS network only' },
  { factor: 'Deductible Savings', allianz: 'Up to 60%', local: 'Limited' },
  { factor: 'Portability', allianz: 'Worldwide', local: 'Costa Rica only' },
  { factor: 'Medical Evacuation', allianz: 'Included', local: 'Not included' },
  { factor: 'Required for Residency', allianz: 'No (CAJA required)', local: 'CAJA required' },
];

const hospitalColumns = [
  { key: 'city', header: 'City' },
  { key: 'hospitals', header: 'Major Network Hospitals' },
  { key: 'directBilling', header: 'Direct Billing' },
];

const hospitalRows = [
  { city: 'San José', hospitals: 'CIMA Hospital, Clínica Bíblica, Hospital La Católica', directBilling: true },
  { city: 'Escazú', hospitals: 'Hospital Metropolitano', directBilling: true },
  { city: 'Heredia', hospitals: 'Hospital Heredia (private wing)', directBilling: true },
  { city: 'Guanacaste', hospitals: 'Clínica Bíblica Santa Cruz', directBilling: true },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Allianz Care Health Insurance in Costa Rica"
  description="Complete guide to using Allianz Care in Costa Rica. High-deductible savings, private hospital access, and how it works with mandatory CAJA."
  headline="Allianz Care Health Insurance in Costa Rica"
  subheadline="High-deductible savings and worldwide coverage for expats in Costa Rica. How Allianz complements the mandatory CAJA system."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/costa-rica-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get an Allianz Costa Rica Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/providers/allianz-care"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Allianz Care in Costa Rica</h2>
  <p>
    Allianz Care offers international coverage for expats in Costa Rica with a standout feature: high-deductible options that can cut premiums by up to 60%. Combined with Costa Rica's affordable healthcare and mandatory CAJA for routine care, this strategy can save significant money.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">2M+</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Providers worldwide</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">60%</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Max deductible savings</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">$5M</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Annual limit available</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get a Costa Rica-Specific Quote"
    description="See what Allianz Care costs with different deductible options."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/allianz-care"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="caja-strategy">CAJA + Allianz Strategy</h2>
  <p>
    The smart approach in Costa Rica is using CAJA for routine care and Allianz for major expenses.
  </p>

  <h3>How This Works</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>CAJA (~$75/mo):</strong> Use for prescriptions, routine visits, basic care</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz with high deductible (~$65-100/mo):</strong> Use for private hospitals, specialists, emergencies</li>
    <li><strong>Total: ~$140-175/mo</strong> for comprehensive coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-2">High-Deductible Makes Sense Here</h3>
    <p class="text-green-800">
      Since CAJA handles routine care and prescriptions, you're unlikely to hit a moderate deductible on Allianz except for major events. A $2,500-5,000 deductible significantly reduces premium while still covering what matters: hospitalization, surgery, cancer treatment.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costa-rica-network">Network Coverage in Costa Rica</h2>
  <p>
    Allianz Care has a good network in Costa Rica, with direct billing at major private hospitals.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={hospitalColumns} rows={hospitalRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Key Network Points</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Central Valley:</strong> Full coverage at CIMA, Clínica Bíblica, Hospital La Católica</li>
    <li><strong>Beach/rural areas:</strong> Limited direct billing; reimbursement model works</li>
    <li><strong>Flexibility:</strong> Use any licensed provider and submit for reimbursement</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <em>Prices for worldwide coverage excluding USA. High deductibles ($2,500-5,000) reduce premiums by 40-60%.</em>
  </p>

  <h3>Which Plan for Costa Rica?</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Essential + High Deductible:</strong> Budget option. Use CAJA for outpatient, Allianz for hospital only.</li>
    <li><strong>Classic:</strong> Balanced choice. Full coverage when you need private care.</li>
    <li><strong>Premium/Platinum:</strong> Maximum coverage for those wanting comprehensive protection.</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Calculate Your Savings"
    description="See how different deductible options affect your premium."
    buttonText="Get a Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/allianz-care"
  />

  <h2 id="vs-local-options">vs Local Options</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Choose Allianz Care If:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>You want high-deductible premium savings</li>
    <li>Worldwide portability matters</li>
    <li>You travel outside Costa Rica</li>
    <li>Medical evacuation is important</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Rely on CAJA + INS If:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Budget is the primary concern</li>
    <li>You don't travel internationally</li>
    <li>You're under 70</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    <a href="/countries/costa-rica/insurance">See all Costa Rica insurance options →</a>
  </p>

  <h2 id="claims">Using Your Insurance in Costa Rica</h2>

  <h3>Direct Billing</h3>
  <p>
    At network hospitals, show your Allianz card for cashless treatment.
  </p>

  <h3>Reimbursement</h3>
  <p>
    For non-network providers, pay and submit via the MyHealth app. Processing typically takes 5 business days.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-its-for">Who Should Choose Allianz in Costa Rica</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Good Fit</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
        <li>Budget-conscious (high-deductible strategy)</li>
        <li>Expats who travel frequently</li>
        <li>Those who might relocate</li>
        <li>People valuing flexibility</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Consider Alternatives</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Those wanting US coverage (Cigna)</li>
        <li>Permanent Costa Rica residents</li>
        <li>Those comfortable with CAJA only</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <h3>Do I still need CAJA with Allianz?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes. CAJA is mandatory for all legal residents. Allianz is a supplement, not a replacement.
  </p>

  <h3>How does the high-deductible work?</h3>
  <p>
    Choose a deductible ($500-$5,000). You pay healthcare costs up to that amount annually. Higher deductible = lower premium. With CAJA handling routine care, you may rarely hit your deductible.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready for Coverage in Costa Rica?"
    description="Get a personalized Allianz Care quote with deductible options."
    buttonText="Get Your Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/allianz-care"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. CAJA requirements change. Verify all information with Allianz Care and Costa Rican authorities.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
